    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-24T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-24T16:00:00-05:00" n="325"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d325">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/267a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Yokohama</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Scidmore</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-24T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 24, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For <persName corresp="#p_SJF1">John F. Stevens</persName> from <persName
                        corresp="#p_WD1">Daniel Willard</persName>: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Your cable 20th. Understand you are with <persName corresp="#p_ECH1"
                                >Emerson</persName> and his force at Nagasaki. It is thought best
                            that you should all remain there for a while and await developments in
                            Russia. Probably inside thirty days definite decision can be reached
                            concerning future course. There is great opportunity for most valuable
                            work for you and <persName corresp="#p_ECH1">Emerson</persName> in
                            Russia, providing stable government is established and think it would be
                            most unfortunate to abandon that plan as long as there is any hope. Have
                            had credit established for you as per your cable December 4 and $50,000
                            for <persName corresp="#p_ECH1">Emerson</persName>. Assume this will
                            keep you both going until definite decision can be reached concerning
                            future. Keep me advised any new developments.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>If <persName corresp="#p_SJF1">Stevens</persName> not at Yokohama forward the
                    above to Nagasaki.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
